    def pandion_rr_gcs_param_load_encode(self, param_id: bytes, param_value: float, param_type: int, stable_crc: int, unstable_crc: int, param_index: int, confirm_send: int) -> MAVLink_pandion_rr_gcs_param_load_message:
        """
        GCS param upload app message that provides parameter definitions,
        stable and unstable crc. At the end of transmission,
        confirm_send is use to indicate the vehicle to save provided
        parameters. For each PANDION_RR_GCS_PARAM_LOAD, the vehicle
        responds with PANDION_RR_GCS_PARAM_LOAD_ACK message below.
        The double param_value is encoded in accordance with
        param_type.

        param_id                  : Onboard parameter id, terminated by NULL if the length is less than 16 human-readable chars and WITHOUT null termination (NULL) byte if the length is exactly 16 chars - applications have to provide 16+1 bytes storage if the ID is stored as string (type:char)
